theorem
(((m <> ( 0 ) & n <> ( 0 )) & ( ( m * m1 ) + ( n * n1 ) ) = k) implies (for x holds (for y holds (( ( m * x ) + ( n * y ) ) = k implies (ex t st (x = ( m1 + ( t * ( n / ( m gcd n ) ) ) ) & y = ( n1 - ( t * ( m / ( m gcd n ) ) ) )))))))
proof
assume that
A1: m <> ( 0 )
and
A2: n <> ( 0 )
and
A3: ( ( m * m1 ) + ( n * n1 ) ) = k;
consider m2,n2 such that A4: m = ( ( m gcd n ) * m2 ) and A5: n = ( ( m gcd n ) * n2 ) and A6: m2,n2 are_relative_prime  by A1,INT_2:23;
A7: ( m gcd n ) <> ( 0 ) by A1,INT_2:5;
then A8: m2 = ( m / ( m gcd n ) ) by A4,XCMPLX_1:89;
A9: n2 = ( n / ( m gcd n ) ) by A7,A5,XCMPLX_1:89;
A10: ( n2 gcd m2 ) = 1 by A6,INT_2:def 3;
let x;
let y;
assume ( ( m * x ) + ( n * y ) ) = k;
then ( m * ( x - m1 ) ) = ( n * ( n1 - y ) ) by A3;
then A11: ( m2 * ( x - m1 ) ) = ( ( n * ( n1 - y ) ) / ( m gcd n ) ) by A8,XCMPLX_1:74
.= ( n2 * ( n1 - y ) ) by A9,XCMPLX_1:74;
then n2 divides ( m2 * ( x - m1 ) ) by INT_1:def 3;
then n2 divides ( x - m1 ) by A10,CKB58:1;
then consider t such that A12: ( n2 * t ) = ( x - m1 ) by INT_1:def 3;
A13: n2 <> ( 0 ) by A2,A5;
then A14: t = ( ( x - m1 ) / n2 ) by A12,XCMPLX_1:89;
A15: m2 <> ( 0 ) by A1,A4;
then ( ( x - m1 ) / n2 ) = ( ( n1 - y ) / m2 ) by A13,A11,XCMPLX_1:94;
then ( t * m2 ) = ( n1 - y ) by A15,A14,XCMPLX_1:87;
then A16: y = ( n1 - ( t * m2 ) );
x = ( m1 + ( t * n2 ) ) by A12;
hence thesis by A8,A9,A16;
end;
